Flub.Name: Apply Autolevel
Flub.Description: Automatically levels the terrain where the heights are proportionately distributed between the highest and lowest points.

Flub.Name: Strength
Flub.Description: The strength of the applied levels method.

Flub.Name: Multiplier
Flub.Description: The strength of the applied raise.

Flub.Name: Apply Log
Flub.Description: Applies logarithmic scaling to the terrain. It works similarly to Autolevel, but uses a logarithmic curve that bulks up the terrain much more.

Flub.Name: Log
Flub.Description: The strength of the log curve.

Flub.Name: Apply Equalize
Flub.Description: Equalizes the terrain where the heights are linearly distributed between the highest and lowest points.

Flub.Name: Apply Gamma
Flub.Description: Applies a Gamma-style height adjustment to the terrain.

Flub.Name: Gamma
Flub.Description: The Gamma amount to be used. This only works when Auto-Gamma is turned off.
